  "description": [
    "FRIDAY JAN 271939 My Say By Evalyn Walsh McLean T3E whole rearmament question that is now before the Congress is the mst important measure it has had before it in many a day When you consider how Utterly unprepared and de fenseless we were when we were hurled into the World War when you consider that the cost of that war to us was about forty or fifty billion dollars when you stop to think if another war should break loose in Europe what the consequences would be in our present state of helpless ness it makes you shudder On the basis of what we spent on the last war we would have to spend around 1150000000000 With the national debt now around 140000000000 this would bring the Indebtedness of the United States to 190000000000 This is almost twothirds of Americas entire wealth as we are rated as being worth approximately 325000000000 In other words unless we can promptly and efficiently give the President and Senator Walsh what they are asking in order to rearm this country in the way it should be in the end we will be running up a far higher debt than by getting ready now"
  ],
